    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>PRECAUTIONS</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Pump shafts are designed to be installed with a slip fit. Pounding will damage the bearings
                        and internal pump parts.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>A pilot (Item 3,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500512">Figure 12</hotlnk>) on the pump mounting flange assures correct mounting and
                shaft alignment. Make sure the pilot is firmly seated in the mounting surface of the power source.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500512" filename="../figg05/g0500512.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Pilot on Pump Mounting Flange</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. KEY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PILOT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Exercise care in tightening the bolts to prevent misalignment.</para>
            <para>If gaskets are used, they must be installed carefully and must lay flat. Shaft key (Item 1,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500512">Figure 12</hotlnk>) and coupling must be properly seated to avoid slipping or
                shearing.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
